          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">everyone !</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to ivy♡ by: </span>
      my father:&gt;
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=made-into-a-movie-or-tv-series">made-into-a-movie-or-tv-series</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=loved">loved</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=south-asian-characters">south-asian-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=ebook">ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=author-of-indian-origin">author-of-indian-origin</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=short">short</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=ownvoices">ownvoices</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90083079-ivy?shelf=classics">classics</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3602495901" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2123537890122189772">you do know that it&apos;s next to impossible for me to properly review a book that i really love, right ? mostly it&apos;s because i feel like putting my love for it down in words is an injustice to this beautiful story.<br/><br/>I&apos;ve tried too many times to review this but i can&apos;t find the words to express how much i loved this story, how much this made me <i>feel</i>. definitely on my list of all - time favourites. what makes this story even more heartbreaking is that it&apos;s based on real - life experiences. i honestly c</span>
  <span id="freeText2123537890122189772" style="display:none">you do know that it's next to impossible for me to properly review a book that i really love, right ? mostly it's because i feel like putting my love for it down in words is an injustice to this beautiful story.<br /><br />I've tried too many times to review this but i can't find the words to express how much i loved this story, how much this made me <i>feel</i>. definitely on my list of all - time favourites. what makes this story even more heartbreaking is that it's based on real - life experiences. i honestly cannot remember the last time i got this emotional over a book; heck, i usually feel stuff but it's always in my head, not something that brings tears to my eyes quite literally.<br /><br />this is the story of a man who has been broken, holding on to only his faith in god and desire to live, completely alienated from normal life. the story of a man who has given up the will to live so many times, whose dreams have shattered too many times.<br /><br />i don't know why this affected me as much as it did. maybe it was because i am a keralite just like our protagonist ? maybe because i too once lived in the middle east ( not in conditions as horrifying as our mc's, not even close ). maybe because some times my faith and will to go on living are thoughts that encourage me to go on living too ? i don't know. <br /><br />i'd read one of benyamin's other works, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/40772676.Jasmine_Days" title="Jasmine Days by Benyamin" rel="nofollow noopener">Jasmine Days</a>, but this story definitely beats it. the language and the writing used in this book is very simple, a stark contrast to the beautiful kaleidoscope of emotions it both portrays as well as evokes from us. when najeeb gets captured, we are not just afraid for him, we're afraid <i>with</i> him. when he gets numerous opportunities to escape, we're as hopeful with him. when he finds solace with the goats he's meant to herd, we get attached to them too.<br /><br />seriously, i <i>need</i> you all to read this. it's too good. it's well - known in kerala, but it's shocking that not many know about this book outside the state. <br /><br />in short, READ THIS ! NOW !<br /><br />* goes back to ugly - cry into my pillow because...* ...yeah, go read it <br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="2123537890122189772" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


