  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2373290245" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2373290245" />
    <a title="Smitha Murthy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3547543-smitha-murthy"><img alt="Smitha Murthy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1632734473p2/3547543.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2373290245?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Smitha Murthy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Smitha Murthy" href="/user/show/3547543-smitha-murthy">Smitha Murthy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780143416333" href="/book/show/15849749-goat-days">review of another edition</a>


          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Smitha by: </span>
      <a href="/user/show/2992522-swati">Swati</a>
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=india">india</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=india-translated">india-translated</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=asia">asia</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3547543-smitha-murthy?shelf=contemporary">contemporary</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2373290245" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17252149892130542763">Many years ago, I remember my friend talking to me about &apos;Goat Days&apos;. I remember the conversation, but I didn&apos;t remember to read the book. When I got around to it last week, my reading was interrupted by travel, and there were times I wished I could just go curl up with this book with no interruptions. This book deserved that sort of undivided time. <br/><br/>Once, while climbing Jordan&apos;s highest mountain, we wandered into Saudi Arabia. My cellphone switched from Jordan&apos;s reception to Saudi Arabia. There </span>
  <span id="freeText17252149892130542763" style="display:none">Many years ago, I remember my friend talking to me about 'Goat Days'. I remember the conversation, but I didn't remember to read the book. When I got around to it last week, my reading was interrupted by travel, and there were times I wished I could just go curl up with this book with no interruptions. This book deserved that sort of undivided time. <br /><br />Once, while climbing Jordan's highest mountain, we wandered into Saudi Arabia. My cellphone switched from Jordan's reception to Saudi Arabia. There were no patrols. We stood there, wind billowing watching over the vast, never-ending desert landscape with our Arab guide. That moment came back to me when I read 'Goat Days' because Benyamin brings that landscape to life with such utter poignancy. The character of Najeeb is based on a real Najeeb, and while I don't know how many stories like Najeeb's exist out there in the world, the story that was depicted here was at once heartbreaking and heartwarming. <br /><br />There was despair, and told in the first-person, the narrator speaks to you as a friend would. You feel that despair. You laugh with Najeeb when he laughs and cry with him when he cries. You wander the masara (the goat pen), lie down with the goats when the desert cold hits you, and try in vain to find respite from the searing heat of the day. Vivid, memorable, and searing, this book is a must-read from Malayalam literature. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17252149892130542763" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
